  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Dice your <strong>potato[es] </strong>(skin on) finely</p><p>Peel and chop 3/4 of your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced potatoes </strong>and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, roughly chop your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Cut your <strong>lime[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Then cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>coriander</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and the juice of half your <strong>lime[s]</strong></p><p>Blitz until well combined – this is your <strong>aguachile-style dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tortillas </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 6-8 min or until lightly browned and crisp – these are your <strong>tostadas</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain then add your <strong>king prawns</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the prawns are cooking, add the <strong>aguachile-style dressing </strong>to a large bowl with the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>sliced cucumber</strong></p><p>Once cooked, add the <strong>king prawns </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>aguachile-style king prawns</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aguachile-style-king-prawn-tostadas/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, add the <strong>roasted potatoes & onion</strong> to the <strong>tostadas</strong> and top with the <strong>aguachile-style king prawns</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
